PITSO Mosimane was hauled before the Al Ahly board through a video call meeting on Tuesday night, according to president, Mahmoud El Khatib. "The meeting will see the presence of Al Ahly Football Company board, headed by Yasseen Mansour, Hossam Ghaly, the club’s board member, and the club’s planning committee members, Mohsen Saleh and Zakaria Nassef. The meeting will discuss some points regarding the first team’s preparations for the upcoming period," said the club in a statement. Indications are that Mosimane is expected to give his plans for the next for next season, and set goals for the coming football term. Mosimane is current in South Africa where he held a mediaa briefing on Monday where shared his views about the cluc's Champions League loss to Raja Casablance in the final.